  "content": ">\n        <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-amber); margin-bottom: 4px;\">CPU</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;\">ORT default. Just works.</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <!-- OpenVINO -->\n    <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 20px; align-items: flex-start;\">\n      <div style=\"min-width: 100px; text-align: center; flex-shrink: 0;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size: 36px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent-red);\">13</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 600;\">PACKAGES</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-red); border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; padding: 20px 24px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-cyan); margin-bottom: 6px;\">Intel iGPU (OpenVINO)</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;\">\n          5 Intel compute-runtime packages &bull; 3 libtbb .debs cross-pulled from Ubuntu Noble (not in Debian Trixie) &bull; 3 OpenVINO libs from Intel apt repo &bull; manual symlinks because APT installs to /usr/lib/ but ORT checks /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/ &bull; /dev/dri by-path symlinks for GPU discovery\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>",
